            <title>[JDK-8300818] Reduce complexity of padding with DateTimeFormatter</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8300818</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Currently it&amp;#39;s O(n) - we do `n` shifts of bytes within `StringBuilder`. This can be reduced to O(1) improving the code like:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
DateTimeFormatter dtf = new DateTimeFormatterBuilder()&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;.appendLiteral(&amp;quot;Date:&amp;quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;.padNext(50, &amp;#39;\t&amp;#39;)&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;.append(DateTimeFormatter.ISO_DATE)&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;.toFormatter();&lt;br/&gt;
String text = dtf.format(LocalDateTime.now());</description>
